    "collapsible_content_JN3rhi": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long does it take to see results with Reviv?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Most users begin noticing improvements within the first few weeks, though the timeline varies based on your specific condition. <br/><br/>Some experience reduced pain and improved jaw mobility within days, while others with more severe or long-term TMJ issues may take 2-3 months to see significant changes. <br/><br/>Remember that Reviv addresses the root cause rather than just masking symptoms, so the healing process is gradual but leads to lasting improvements.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tUj3HX": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will Reviv work if I've tried other TMJ treatments without success?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>We cannot promise anything.</p><p>But wearing a mouthguard is a very cheap and easy thing to test.</p><p>So I personally view it as being worth a try.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_6bErhk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is Reviv uncomfortable to wear?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes it can be uncomfortable to wear at times.  Especially at the beginning.</p><p>Sometimes there will be pain in the teeth or gums.</p><p>And some folks might get headaches.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_jEbzGk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do I need to wear Reviv forever?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Generally the teeth will extrude to close the posterior open bite that is created when improving curve of spee.</p><p>But you should continue to wear the mouthguard till that happens.</p><p>Or you can get composite as discussed here:  https://reviv.substack.com/p/the-mystery-around-posterior-open </p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
